init_text: An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The aliens let out a sigh and picked up the phone, dialing Matt Damon's agent.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Commander, "I don't care how many times a day they call us.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Everytime they tried to run out of range, a new call would come in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "How long do you think they can last like this?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But the commander shook his head.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I promised her I would bring him home.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I had heard about this scam call plague before we left and I was sure it would be taken care of by the time we got back."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: and they made the decision to turn back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The crew grew soft and coddled the earthling.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Off in the distance, Matt Damon's agent could be seen holding a large check, laughing hysterically.
